Modifications from the original Heretic codebase include but are not
limited to:

  - Multi-objective Optuna TPE optimization (co-minimizing refusals and
    KL divergence)
  - LoRA-based steering instead of destructive weight modification
  - Orthogonal projection of steering vectors against benign directions
  - Mixture-of-Experts (MoE) support: expert profiling, router weight
    suppression, and fused expert abliteration
  - LLM judge refusal detection via OpenRouter
  - Support for additional architectures: LiquidAI LFM2 (hybrid
    conv+attention), GLM-4 MoE (MLA), Devstral, MiniMax-M2.5, GPT-OSS
  - Fractional direction index and per-component abliteration parameters
  - Auto batch sizing and KL divergence pruning
  - Research visualization tools (PaCMAP residual plots)
  - TOML-based configuration system
  - Comprehensive test suite
